♪ There's a part of me,
a part of me ♪

36:45.380 --> 36:48.120
Oh. Is he, uh...doing o--

36:48.120 --> 36:49.920
He's stable.

36:49.920 --> 36:51.330
Came off his vents
easily.

36:51.330 --> 36:52.960
We won't know more
'til he wakes up,

36:52.960 --> 36:55.920
but that implant was basically
rotted inside of him.

36:55.920 --> 36:58.830
It was, uh...awful.

36:58.830 --> 37:02.290
♪ Wishing on the brightest,
brightest star ♪
[ Sighs ]

37:02.290 --> 37:06.710
♪ But nothing ever really
feels that far ♪

37:06.710 --> 37:10.540
♪ I'm following the burning,
burning sun ♪

37:10.540 --> 37:12.960
♪ Around and around
and here I come ♪

37:12.960 --> 37:14.670
Okay.

37:14.670 --> 37:16.620
When he wakes up,
make sure his pain's controlled

37:16.620 --> 37:17.830
and walk him through
his recovery.

37:17.830 --> 37:19.710
And tell him he missed
his chance at the majors

37:19.710 --> 37:21.460
and his dream is dead.

37:21.460 --> 37:23.710
Schmitt, you're not the one
who's suffering here.

37:23.710 --> 37:25.670
He is.

37:25.670 --> 37:27.330
So put on a game face,
suck up your feelings,
'cause that's what we do.

37:27.330 --> 37:29.920
If you can't do that,
if you can't do your job...

37:29.920 --> 37:31.420
consider a new career.

37:31.420 --> 37:34.380
♪ Cloud, cloud chaser ♪

37:34.380 --> 37:42.500
♪♪

37:42.500 --> 37:45.960
♪ I know just what I want,
I know just where I want to go ♪

37:45.960 --> 37:47.960
♪ And who I want to be ♪

37:47.960 --> 37:49.330
♪ I want to be ♪

37:49.330 --> 37:50.250
Teddy: [ Breathing heavily ]

37:50.250 --> 37:52.750
♪ I'm a cloud, cloud chaser ♪

37:52.750 --> 37:54.710
[ Moans ]

37:54.710 --> 37:56.710
Oh, God.

37:56.710 --> 37:58.580
Oh, God.

37:58.580 --> 38:00.790
Oh, yes.

38:00.790 --> 38:02.920
Oh!

38:02.920 --> 38:04.620
God!

38:04.620 --> 38:06.080
Oh!

38:06.080 --> 38:07.170
Oh.

38:07.170 --> 38:08.830
Koracick: Mm. Mm.

38:08.830 --> 38:10.040
[ Smooching ]

38:10.040 --> 38:12.460
Oh, God. Oh.

38:12.460 --> 38:14.420
Let's not wait 'til 7:00.
Let's leave now.

38:14.420 --> 38:16.620
No, I can't.
[ Breathing heavily ]

38:16.620 --> 38:17.620
I can't leave with you.

38:17.620 --> 38:19.540
I c--

38:19.540 --> 38:23.040
I'm...I am marrying Owen.

38:23.040 --> 38:24.710
This was...

38:24.710 --> 38:26.920
This was goodbye.

38:31.500 --> 38:35.120
♪♪

38:35.120 --> 38:43.620
♪♪

38:46.830 --> 38:48.040
Okay.

38:48.040 --> 38:51.670
Mm. Mm.

38:51.670 --> 38:53.420
How's that?

38:53.420 --> 38:55.620
Ah.

38:55.620 --> 38:56.790
Thank you, Maggie.

38:58.170 --> 39:00.880
It's so nice
to hear you say my name.

39:00.880 --> 39:04.380
♪♪

39:04.380 --> 39:05.920
Do you know
who this is?

39:07.750 --> 39:11.040
Mm.
You mean, um...Jackson?

39:11.040 --> 39:14.330
Hey, Richard.

39:14.330 --> 39:16.210
Do you know
where you are?

39:16.210 --> 39:19.620
Grey-Sloan Memorial?

39:19.620 --> 39:21.380
If this is a quiz,

39:21.380 --> 39:24.580
you might want to ask
some tougher questions.

39:24.580 --> 39:26.670
[ Chuckles ]

39:26.670 --> 39:28.120
Jackson: Fair enough.

39:28.120 --> 39:30.250
Okay, um, hold out
your hand for me.

39:30.250 --> 39:35.120
♪♪

39:35.120 --> 39:36.080
[ Exhales sharply ]

39:36.080 --> 39:37.540
[ Exhales sharply ]

39:37.540 --> 39:39.380
♪♪

39:39.380 --> 39:41.040
Oh, sweetheart.

39:41.040 --> 39:42.830
The nurses
are gonna bring in a bed

39:42.830 --> 39:45.080
so I can stay the night
with you.

39:47.420 --> 39:48.960
It's Catherine.
It's -- It's Mom.

39:48.960 --> 39:50.710
I know who it is.

39:50.710 --> 39:51.830
What is she doing here?

39:51.830 --> 39:53.250
Sweetheart.

39:53.250 --> 39:55.120
I've been with you
this whole time.

39:55.120 --> 39:56.960
Is your mind
playing tricks on you again?

39:59.170 --> 40:01.420
Did you stand by me
while I was being fired,

40:01.420 --> 40:03.790
you buy my hospital
to humiliate me,

40:03.790 --> 40:05.710
or is that my mind
playing tricks, too?

40:05.710 --> 40:06.790
Richard, calm down.

40:06.790 --> 40:07.880
Get out.

40:07.880 --> 40:09.620
Richard.
Okay, Mom, let's go.

40:09.620 --> 40:12.290
Let's give him a little --
little bit of time. Okay?
Richard.

40:12.290 --> 40:14.420
[ Sighs ]

40:14.420 --> 40:16.540
Meredith: Sometimes, surgeries
go better than planned.

40:16.540 --> 40:19.420
♪♪

40:19.420 --> 40:21.290
Grey.

40:21.290 --> 40:23.120
Heard about Webber.

40:23.120 --> 40:24.540
Oh, yeah.
Incredible catch.

40:24.540 --> 40:27.750
Yeah,
it was...not all me.

40:27.750 --> 40:30.460
It was an army
and mainly DeLuca.

40:30.460 --> 40:32.170
Mm-hmm.

40:32.170 --> 40:34.170
Want to grab a drink?
Celebrate?

40:34.170 --> 40:35.620
Yes.

40:35.620 --> 40:39.080
Except
I'm so exhausted.

40:39.080 --> 40:40.920
Will you ask me
another time?

40:40.920 --> 40:42.250
Of course.
See you later.

40:42.250 --> 40:43.500
Bye.

40:43.500 --> 40:45.540
♪ Place to belong ♪

40:47.250 --> 40:49.750
♪ I'm already gone ♪

40:49.750 --> 40:52.000
Hey. Andrew?

40:52.000 --> 40:54.460
♪ We're the lonely hearts club ♪

40:54.460 --> 40:56.710
♪ We're losing in love ♪

40:56.710 --> 40:57.580
♪ We're shaking it... ♪

40:57.580 --> 40:59.170
Andrew, it's over.

40:59.170 --> 41:01.500
Maggie said she'll call us
if there are any changes.

41:01.500 --> 41:03.040
♪ We're the lonely hearts club ♪

41:03.040 --> 41:07.170
[ Voice breaking ]
I don't -- I can't, uh...

41:07.170 --> 41:08.120
I don't know
what's going on.

41:08.120 --> 41:09.750
Okay, okay.

41:09.750 --> 41:11.670
Can we just go home?

41:11.670 --> 41:14.920
Let's go home, okay?
Come on.

41:14.920 --> 41:17.460
♪ I was already gone ♪

41:17.460 --> 41:19.080
There's no better gift
you can give someone

41:19.080 --> 41:20.670
than saying you saved
the person they love.

41:20.670 --> 41:22.290
It went okay, I think.

41:22.290 --> 41:25.880
♪ Searching for somebody
and a place to belong ♪

41:25.880 --> 41:27.790
♪ A place to belong ♪

41:27.790 --> 41:29.960
I look forward
to those moments.

41:29.960 --> 41:32.670
♪ We're already gone ♪

41:32.670 --> 41:35.080
Unfortunately, those perfect
outcomes are rare.

41:35.080 --> 41:37.170
♪ We're the lonely hearts club ♪

41:37.170 --> 41:38.500
♪ We're losing in love ♪

41:38.500 --> 41:40.120
You would think it gets easier,
but it doesn't.

41:40.120 --> 41:43.460
♪ ...shaking it,
shaking it off ♪

41:43.460 --> 41:45.170
♪ We're the lonely hearts club ♪

41:45.170 --> 41:48.250
Each one hurts just as much
as the last one.

41:48.250 --> 41:52.120
♪ We're shaking it,
shaking it off ♪

41:52.120 --> 41:54.420
♪ You're the voice in my head ♪

41:54.420 --> 41:56.580
♪ You drive me to bed ♪

41:56.580 --> 41:58.710
♪ You make my decisions ♪

41:58.710 --> 42:01.080
♪ No, you don't listen ♪

42:01.080 --> 42:03.500
♪ You don't listen ♪

42:03.500 --> 42:05.580
So, we hope for the best...

42:05.580 --> 42:08.040
♪ You don't listen ♪

42:08.040 --> 42:09.620
...and prepare for the worst.

42:09.620 --> 42:13.040
♪♪

42:13.040 --> 42:14.290
Hey, Teddy.

42:14.290 --> 42:17.540
I'm so sorry, honey.
We'll reschedule.

42:17.540 --> 42:18.790
♪ We're the lonely hearts club ♪

42:18.790 --> 42:22.330
Alison just fell asleep,
and I'll get that guy down.

42:22.330 --> 42:25.710
[ Exhales sharply ]
Why are we rescheduling?

42:25.710 --> 42:28.330
Owen got pulled in
for a last-minute surgery.

42:28.330 --> 42:30.420
Said to send everyone home.
He didn't call you?

42:30.420 --> 42:31.880
♪ We're shaking it... ♪

42:31.880 --> 42:33.330
No.

42:33.330 --> 42:35.420
Oh, well, seems he barely
had time to tell me.

42:35.420 --> 42:38.290
I mean, trauma -- well,
you know better than anyone.

42:38.290 --> 42:40.080
♪ Lonely hearts club ♪

42:40.080 --> 42:41.620
Right.

42:43.250 --> 42:46.500
Because the worst
has a nasty way of finding you.

42:46.500 --> 42:48.330
♪ Lonely hearts club ♪

42:48.330 --> 42:50.670
♪ Lonely hearts club ♪

42:50.670 --> 42:52.830
♪♪

